    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So I finally worked on that. And the good news is that it can be fixed in newer versions too. But first I'd like to let you know we're very sorry that you had the issue in the first place and I'd like to thank you for your patience.\r\n\r\nSo what happens is that the URL mechanics detects a change and therefore update the URL. That's the expected behavior. What is less expected is that this change happens in the searchfunction itself. That's why we have an update when the pages is first loaded. However there is a fix for that. Because we don't want changes at this moment, the initial state should be the same. And there is an option on the instantsearch function: searchParameters. Here is how I fixed your example:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n        var search = instantsearch({\r\n          appId: 'latency',\r\n          apiKey: '6be0576ff61c053d5f9a3225e2a90f76',\r\n          indexName: 'movies',\r\n          searchParameters: {\r\n            facets: [\r\n              'genre'\r\n            ],\r\n+           facetsRefinements: {\r\n+            genre: ['Drama']\r\n+           }\r\n+         },\r\n          searchFunction: function(helper) {\r\n            helper.addFacetRefinement('genre', 'Drama');\r\n\r\n            helper.search();\r\n          },\r\n          urlSync: true\r\n        });\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can see the [result here](http://unadvised-sack.surge.sh/index-noNewURL.html) and the [original here](http://unadvised-sack.surge.sh).\r\n\r\nI think we should close this issue, WDYT @austin-roberts ?",
